Note: P2-D Q4 FFI Foundation Smoke Test — Unsafe External Call OUTSIDE Unsafe Block
Note:
Note: Per CEO Q4 amendment 2026-05-24, calling an unsafe External outside an
Note: Unsafe Block must produce a compile-time error with the exact message:
Note:   "Cannot call unsafe External 'raw_syscall' outside an Unsafe Block.
Note:    Wrap the call site in 'Unsafe Block: ... End Unsafe'."
Note:
Note: Expected output:
Note:   - Compilation: HARD ERROR (exit nonzero)
Note:   - Error message contains the rejection diagnostic

unsafe External Process called "raw_syscall"
    that takes syscall_no as Integer
    returns Integer
    from library "c"
    convention c

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Note: Calling raw_syscall OUTSIDE an Unsafe Block must trigger the
    Note: P2-D Q4 active-rejection diagnostic. The compiler must NOT
    Note: emit a binary; this file's purpose is to verify the rejection.
    Let result be raw_syscall(39)
    Return result
End Process
